page.title: 10 MUIRHEAD
page.content: Muirhead is the most heavily populated area in our block.It has a post office, a police station, a school, a garage, a scout hall, church and three shops.There is also a large wood called Backmuir wood which contains a large selection of wildlife such as deer, rabbits, birds and many others.There is a population in excess of 1500 people.Muirhead is a traditional village, not like Liff or Fowlis with plenty of recreation facilities such as the park which has two football pitches and some play apparatus and also a tennis court.Next door to this is situated a bowling green.
